 CMAT：“人们渴望另一种观点” https://www.nme.com/news/music/cmat-interview-mercury-prize-new-music-oasis-jedward-3792383?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=cmat-interview-mercury-prize-new-music-绿洲-杰德沃德Liberty DunworthTue, 10 Sep 2024 16:22:45 +0000 Music InterviewsMusic NewsNewsCountryMercury PrizePop https://www.nme.com/?p=3792383 <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/CMAT@2000x1270.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="CMAT 出席在 Abbey Road Studios 举行的 2024 年水星音乐奖" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/CMAT@2000x1270.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/CMAT@2000x1270-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/CMAT@2000x1270-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/CMAT@2000x1270-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/CMAT@2000x1270-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/CMAT@2000x1270-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p>这位爱尔兰歌手兼词曲作者讲述了“很少的文化资助”如何影响新音乐，她为获得三场绿洲演出门票所做的“可怕的事情”，以及为什么杰德沃德受到如此误解</p><p><a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/cmat-interview-mercury-prize-new-music-oasis-jedward-3792383">CMAT 帖子：“人们渴望另一种观点”</a>首先出现在<a href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a>上。</p> ; <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/CMAT@2000x1270.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="CMAT 出席在 Abbey Road Studios 举行的 2024 年水星音乐奖" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/CMAT@2000x1270.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/CMAT@2000x1270-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/CMAT@2000x1270-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/CMAT@2000x1270-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/CMAT@2000x1270-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/CMAT@2000x1270-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/cmat">CMAT</a>向<em>《NME》</em>讲述了如此多的新音乐如何向“渴望另类观点”的观众带来突破。</p><ul><li><strong>阅读更多： <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/cmat-interview-ireland-new-music-ivors-album-3759488">CMAT：“爱尔兰人一直都很出色——但也有很多创伤”</a></strong></li></ul><p>这位爱尔兰歌手兼作曲家在今年的<a href="https://www.nme.com/tag/mercury-prize">水星奖</a>红毯上追上了<em>NME</em> ，她的 2023 年专辑<a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/album/cmat-crazymad-for-me-review-lyrics-tracklist-3512398">《Crazymad, For Me</a> <a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/album/cmat-crazymad-for-me-review-lyrics-tracklist-3512398">》</a>入围，并面临着来自<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/charli-xcx">Charli XCX</a> 、 <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/the-last-dinner-party">The Last Evening Party</a> 、 <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/ghetts">Ghetts 等</a>乐队的激烈竞争。 、<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/corinne-bailey-rae">科琳·贝利·雷</a>、<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/beth-gibbons">贝丝·吉本斯</a>、<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/barry-cant-swim">巴里不会游泳</a>等。</p><p>然而，在上周四（9 月 5 日）的 Abbey Road 颁奖典礼上，获胜者是利兹乐队和前<a href="https://www.nme.com/features/the-cover/the-cover-english-teacher-the-worlds-biggest-paving-slab-3495785"><em>NME</em>封面明星</a><a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/english-teacher-win-the-2024-mercury-prize-for-this-could-be-texas-3791098">英语老师</a>。这次胜利使他们成为十年来第一位非伦敦获奖者。</p><p>在获胜之前，CMAT（真名 Ciara Mary-Alice Thompson）回顾了今年入围的首张专辑的数量，并解释了它如何反映了 2024 年歌迷的需求。</p><p> “有很多真正有创意的事情发生，因为一开始感觉成为音乐表演比以往任何时候都更困难，”她说。 “文化资金很少，还有生活成本等等，以前有很多来自非常富裕背景的非常富有的人在做音乐。”</p><p>她继续说道：“但现在确实感觉正在突破的是那些极度渴望在音乐中表达想法的人们。这已经成为人们关注的焦点，我认为这是因为人们渴望另一种观点。对我来说，这就是为什么现在有如此多令人兴奋的新音乐出现。” </p><blockquote class="instagram-media" data-instgrm-captioned data-instgrm-permalink="https://www.instagram.com/reel/C_nQ1pXS2oH/?utm_source=ig_embed&amp;utm_campaign=loading" data-instgrm-version="14" style=" background:#FF